# CHAPTER 3: PROJECT DESCRIPTION (~12 pages)

---

## 3.1 Front End

The frontend of the Autonomous ML Lifecycle Platform is built using **Vite + React (JSX)** — a modern, fast, and lightweight JavaScript framework for building interactive user interfaces. The frontend communicates with the FastAPI backend via RESTful API calls using Axios.

### 3.1.1 Technologies Used

| Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|
| React (JSX) | Component-based UI framework |
| Vite | Build tool and development server with Hot Module Replacement (HMR) |
| Axios | HTTP client for API communication |
| React Router | Client-side routing for single-page application navigation |
| Recharts / Chart.js | Data visualization (bar charts, line charts, pie charts) |
| CSS (Vanilla) | Styling with modern design patterns |

### 3.1.2 Frontend Pages

The frontend consists of **8 dedicated pages**, each providing a specific functional capability:

**1. Dashboard Page ([Dashboard.jsx](file:///c:/Users/nithi/Projects/autonomous-ml-platform/automl-frontend/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx) — 24,701 bytes)**

The main entry point of the application. Provides a system-level overview including:
- Active model count and health status
- Recent drift score trends with visual indicators
- Key performance metrics at a glance
- Recent automation decisions and their outcomes
- Quick navigation links to detailed sections

**2. Dataset Upload Page ([DatasetUpload.jsx](file:///c:/Users/nithi/Projects/autonomous-ml-platform/automl-frontend/src/pages/DatasetUpload.jsx) — 21,737 bytes)**

Allows users to upload CSV datasets and view profiling results:
- Drag-and-drop or file browser-based CSV upload
- Automatic column schema extraction and display
- Baseline statistics visualization (mean, standard deviation, missing count per feature)
- Dataset metadata display (row count, column count, data types)

**3. Models Page ([Models.jsx](file:///c:/Users/nithi/Projects/autonomous-ml-platform/automl-frontend/src/pages/Models.jsx) — 27,063 bytes)**

Comprehensive model registry browser:
- List of all registered models with status indicators (active/inactive/archived)
- Version history timeline with expandable metadata
- Model promotion and rollback capabilities
- Side-by-side version comparison
- Framework and model class information

**4. Training Page ([Training.jsx](file:///c:/Users/nithi/Projects/autonomous-ml-platform/automl-frontend/src/pages/Training.jsx) — 35,990 bytes)**

Training job management interface:
- Training configuration form with strategy selection
- Real-time job status tracking (queued/running/completed/failed)
- Training logs and progress visualization
- Hyperparameter search results and convergence plots
- Feature selection results and model leaderboard

**5. Inference Page ([Inference.jsx](file:///c:/Users/nithi/Projects/autonomous-ml-platform/automl-frontend/src/pages/Inference.jsx) — 37,329 bytes)**

Live prediction interface:
- Feature input form dynamically generated from model schema
- Real-time prediction results with confidence scores
- Request/response logging table
- Latency metrics visualization
- Historical inference log browser

**6. Monitoring Page ([Monitoring.jsx](file:///c:/Users/nithi/Projects/autonomous-ml-platform/automl-frontend/src/pages/Monitoring.jsx) — 35,302 bytes)**

Real-time drift monitoring dashboard:
- Global drift score gauge with severity coloring
- Per-feature drift breakdown with bar charts
- Performance trend line charts
- Alert log with severity classification
- Monitoring signal history

**7. Automation Page ([Automation.jsx](file:///c:/Users/nithi/Projects/autonomous-ml-platform/automl-frontend/src/pages/Automation.jsx) — 44,371 bytes)**

LLM decision and autonomous retraining management:
- Decision log with LLM analysis text
- Automation trigger buttons for manual drift checks
- Execution status tracking (pending/approved/executing/completed)
- Approval workflow interface for high-severity decisions
- Complete automation audit trail

**8. Policies Page ([Policies.jsx](file:///c:/Users/nithi/Projects/autonomous-ml-platform/automl-frontend/src/pages/Policies.jsx) — 27,964 bytes)**

Guardrail and policy configuration:
- Freeze window management (start/end dates)
- GPU and cost limit configuration
- Retraining rate limit settings
- Severity-based auto-approval rules
- Confidence threshold adjustment
- Policy rule enable/disable toggles

