## 3.2 Back End

The backend is built using **FastAPI**, a modern, high-performance Python web framework with native async support. It handles all server-side logic including data processing, model training, inference serving, drift monitoring, LLM interaction, policy evaluation, and automation orchestration.

### 3.2.1 Technologies Used

**Table 3.1: Technology Stack Summary**

| Technology | Version | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| FastAPI | Latest | Asynchronous REST API framework |
| Uvicorn | Standard | ASGI server for FastAPI |
| SQLAlchemy | Latest | Async ORM for PostgreSQL |
| asyncpg | Latest | Async PostgreSQL driver |
| PostgreSQL | 15 | Relational database for metadata, logs, and states |
| MinIO | Latest | S3-compatible object storage for models and datasets |
| Ollama + LLaMA3 | Latest | Local LLM inference server |
| scikit-learn | Latest | Machine learning model training and evaluation |
| XGBoost | Latest | Gradient boosting model training |
| Optuna | Latest | Bayesian hyperparameter optimization |
| imbalanced-learn | Latest | SMOTE for class imbalance handling |
| Pandas | Latest | Data manipulation and analysis |
| joblib | Latest | Model serialization |
| Prometheus Client | Latest | Metrics exposition for observability |
| HTTPX | Latest | Async HTTP client for Ollama API calls |
| APScheduler | Latest | Background job scheduling for monitoring |
| Docker | Latest | Containerization and training isolation |

### 3.2.2 Backend Architecture

The backend follows a **layered service architecture**:

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    API Layer (FastAPI)                     │
│   Routes: datasets, models, training, inference,          │
│           monitoring, automation, policies                │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                   Service Layer                           │
│   DatasetService, ModelRegistryService, InferenceService,│
│   MonitoringService, LLMDecisionEngine, PolicyEvaluator, │
│   TrainingOrchestrator, TrainingRunner, ModelEvaluator,  │
│   AutomationExecutor, ModelServingService, SignalService  │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                    Data Layer                             │
│   SQLAlchemy Models → PostgreSQL (asyncpg)               │
│   MinIO Client → Object Storage                          │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                 Infrastructure Layer                      │
│   Docker Compose, Prometheus, APScheduler                │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### 3.2.3 API Endpoints

The backend exposes RESTful endpoints organized by resource:

| Endpoint Group | Base Path | Key Operations |
|---|---|---|
| Datasets | `/api/datasets` | Upload, list, get details, get statistics |
| Models | `/api/models` | Register, list, get versions, promote, rollback |
| Training | `/api/training` | Start job, get status, list jobs, get results |
| Inference | `/api/inference` | Predict, list logs, get metrics |
| Monitoring | `/api/monitoring` | Trigger check, get metrics, get alerts |
| Automation | `/api/automation` | Get decisions, approve/reject, execute, get logs |
| Policies | `/api/policies` | Create, update, list, enable/disable rules |

