## 3.7 Database Design

The platform uses **PostgreSQL 15** with async access via **SQLAlchemy + asyncpg**. The database contains 9 tables, each serving a specific data management purpose.

**Table 3.2: Database Schema Overview**

### Table 1: `datasets`

| Column | Data Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| id | UUID (PK) | Unique dataset identifier |
| name | VARCHAR | Human-readable dataset name |
| file_path | VARCHAR | MinIO storage path (`datasets/{id}.csv`) |
| column_schema | JSONB | Extracted column names and data types |
| baseline_stats | JSONB | Per-column mean, std, and missing count |
| row_count | INTEGER | Number of rows in the dataset |
| created_at | TIMESTAMP | Upload timestamp |

### Table 2: `model_registry`

| Column | Data Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| id | UUID (PK) | Unique model identifier |
| name | VARCHAR | Model name |
| dataset_id | UUID (FK) | Reference to datasets table |
| framework | VARCHAR | ML framework (e.g., `sklearn`) |
| model_class | VARCHAR | Model class (e.g., `RandomForestClassifier`) |
| current_version | INTEGER | Active production version number |
| status | VARCHAR | Lifecycle state: active/inactive/archived |
| created_at | TIMESTAMP | Registration timestamp |

### Table 3: `model_versions`

| Column | Data Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| id | UUID (PK) | Unique version identifier |
| model_id | UUID (FK) | Reference to model_registry table |
| version_number | INTEGER | Sequential version number (v1, v2, ...) |
| artifact_path | VARCHAR | MinIO path to serialized model |
| metrics | JSONB | Accuracy, F1, R², MSE, leaderboard, etc. |
| hyperparameters | JSONB | Best hyperparameters from training |
| parent_version | INTEGER | Parent version number (lineage tracking) |
| training_job_id | UUID (FK) | Reference to training_jobs table |
| created_at | TIMESTAMP | Version creation timestamp |

### Table 4: `training_jobs`

| Column | Data Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| id | UUID (PK) | Unique job identifier |
| model_id | UUID (FK) | Reference to model_registry table |
| status | VARCHAR | queued/running/completed/failed/early_stopped |
| config | JSONB | Training configuration (strategy, phases, params) |
| result_metrics | JSONB | Training results and evaluation metrics |
| started_at | TIMESTAMP | Job start timestamp |
| completed_at | TIMESTAMP | Job completion timestamp |

### Table 5: `inference_logs`

| Column | Data Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| id | UUID (PK) | Unique log entry identifier |
| model_id | UUID (FK) | Reference to model_registry table |
| input_features | JSONB | Input feature values for the prediction |
| prediction | VARCHAR | Model prediction output |
| latency_ms | FLOAT | Inference latency in milliseconds |
| version_number | INTEGER | Model version used for prediction |
| created_at | TIMESTAMP | Inference timestamp |

### Table 6: `monitoring_metrics`

| Column | Data Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| id | UUID (PK) | Unique metric record identifier |
| model_id | UUID (FK) | Reference to model_registry table |
| drift_score | FLOAT | Global drift score (0 to 1) |
| feature_drifts | JSONB | Per-feature drift breakdown |
| performance_delta | FLOAT | Change in model performance |
| request_count | INTEGER | Number of recent inference requests |
| avg_latency | FLOAT | Average inference latency (ms) |
| severity | VARCHAR | low/medium/high/critical |
| created_at | TIMESTAMP | Monitoring check timestamp |

### Table 7: `automation_logs`

| Column | Data Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| id | UUID (PK) | Unique log entry identifier |
| model_id | UUID (FK) | Reference to model_registry table |
| event_type | VARCHAR | Alert/decision/execution/lifecycle event type |
| details | JSONB | Full event metadata and reasoning |
| action | VARCHAR | Action taken (RETRAIN/ALERT/PROMOTE/etc.) |
| status | VARCHAR | Event status (pending/approved/executed/blocked) |
| created_at | TIMESTAMP | Event timestamp |

### Table 8: `automation_state`

| Column | Data Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| id | UUID (PK) | Unique state identifier |
| model_id | UUID (FK) | Reference to model_registry table |
| last_action | VARCHAR | Most recent action performed |
| last_action_time | TIMESTAMP | Timestamp of last action |
| cooldown_until | TIMESTAMP | Cooldown expiry time |
| consecutive_count | INTEGER | Count of consecutive same-type actions |

### Table 9: `policies`

| Column | Data Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| id | UUID (PK) | Unique policy identifier |
| name | VARCHAR | Policy rule name |
| policy_type | VARCHAR | Type (freeze_window/gpu_limit/cost_cap/etc.) |
| config | JSONB | Policy configuration parameters |
| enabled | BOOLEAN | Whether the policy is currently active |
| created_at | TIMESTAMP | Policy creation timestamp |
| updated_at | TIMESTAMP | Last modification timestamp |

